# 1999-08-06.mgs: Debian Trademark in France

August 6th, 1999

The Board of Directors (the "Board") of Software in the Public
Interest, Inc. (the "Company") hereby designates Vincent Renardias to
register the trademark "Debian" in France on behalf of the Company.

Following is a formal letter as needed by Vincent Renardias which will
be sent to him printed:

Vincent Renardias is acting as external consultant of the Company.
The Company hereby allows "Les logiciels du soleil" or one of its
employees to register the Debian trademark in France in the name of
the Company. The trademark will be assigned to:

Software in the Public Interest, Inc.  
PO Box 1326  
Boston, Ma. 02117  
USA
